Improve collection of logs

Function collect_logs now reads all log files in input 'path'. If log files for different isotopes are in 'path', user is prompted for the correct choice, and log files of only the chouce will be read.

Improve file name handling and progress messages

Log file names does not have to start with log_. It is sufficient that log_ is contained in the filename. Updated isotope name extraction accordingly. When creating summary file, progress messages are printed to get a sense on the remaining time needed.

Implement prefactor and level density function parameters

E1, M1, E2 pre-factors can now be specified as function arguments. It is also possible to toggle between using the partial and total level density for the GSF. Warnings are raised if 'wrong' parameters are used.

Implement include_only_nonzero_in_average

Implement parity filter for level_plot

This was actually a bug in the program, that the parity of the level plot was taken as the parity of the ground state, but the function did not have any actual filtering of parity meaning that both + and - were counted as if all were of the ground state parity. Now, the levels are actually filtered based on parity. If no filter is given, then the ground state parity is chosen. The next step is to include both parities in the plot by default, while keeping the possibility of filtering.

Improve line width handling and add alpha channel
